text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The film is directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck, with a screenplay by Boden, Fleck, and Geneva Robertson-Dworet.

Captain Marvel was released on March 8, 2019, and received generally positive reviews from critics, who praised Brie Larson's performance, the visual effects, and the action sequences. It grossed over $1.1 billion worldwide, making it one of the highest-grossing films of 2019.

The film also features Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Annette Bening, Clark Gregg, and Jude Law in supporting roles.

## Plot

In 1989, Kree warrior Vers (Brie Larson) suffers from amnesia and recurring nightmares about her past. She lives on the planet Hala, the capital of the Kree Empire, where she trains under the guidance of Yon-Rogg (Jude Law), the leader of the Starforce, an elite Kree military team.

During a mission to rescue a group of Kree agents captured by the Skrulls, Vers is captured by Talos (Ben Mendelsohn), the leader of the Skrulls, who are shape-shifting aliens.
